name: Extinct
description:
Inktober prompt day 24: Extinct
The Levuana moth is an extinct moth due to the fact that it had a hankering for coconut plants in Fiji back in the 1870s. The coconut plants were a vital source and the moths were purposefully wiped from existence because they fucked up so much of the Fiji coconut economy and the people's way of life who relied so heavily on the plant. Fuck you, Levuana moth. Drawn with pen and ink and added PS brushes.
